Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and separated whites from greens), separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @carrot{3%ounce}. Using a #peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core; discard core. Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. (Skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @ginger{1%thumb}(minced) and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pickled Scallions & Sauce ==

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}; set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} (save the rest for serving).

In a #large pan{}, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} over medium-high heat. Add @carrot{3%ounce}(shaved into ribbons) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add @zucchini{1}(cut into ¼-inch-thick half-moons) and another drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer to bowl with carrot.

Add @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(thinly sliced) and another drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to same bowl. Wipe out pan.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Fried Eggs ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pan over medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, you may want to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Arrange carrot, zucchini, and mushrooms on top. Top each bowl with a fried egg and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Drizzle with sauce and any remaining Sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

> Add chicken or beef to bowls along with fried eggs.